For a quick start, see *_test.py.

I. A quick how-to-use guide:
    1.Choose a predefined network model from Ann.networks
    2.Choose a loss function from Ann.loss_funcs
    3.Use the forward method to predict
    4.Use the loss function to compute gradients
    5.Use backward to perform back-propogation

II. A quick how-to-build-a-model guide:
    0.See examples and comments in Ann.networks
    1.See layers defined in Ann.layers and build a list of layers
    2.Create a child class based on Ann.network_proto.Network
    3.Intialize Ann.network_proto.Network by the layer list
    4.Define set_layer_initializer() to set parameter intialization method for each layer
    5.Define learner() to set parameter updating method
    6.Define regulariser() to set regularisation term
    7.Train and test your network a I.
